{"INCOERCIBLE":[{"def":"Not capable of being reduced to the form of a liquid by pressure; -- said of any gas above its critical point; -- also particularly of oxygen, hydrogen, nitrogen, and carbon monoxide, formerly regarded as incapable of liquefaction at any temperature or pressure.","pos":""},{"def":"That can note be confined in, or excluded from, vessels, like ordinary fluids, gases, etc.","pos":""}],"INCOEXISTENCE":[{"def":"The state of not coexisting.","pos":""}]}